	<div class="page-block page-block-text">
			<div class="placeholder-tinymce-text">
<p>Comal ISD understands that there is a lot of concern among students, staff, and parents related to Covid-19 (coronavirus). District personnel are in contact with local and regional health officials and will follow their guidance with regard to any actions that we may need to take in response to this issue. In the meantime, you can continue to take simple actions to slow the spread of respiratory infections, including:</p>
<ul>
<li>Staying home when sick</li>
<li>Washing your hands often with soap and water</li>
<li>Avoiding touching your face; covering your cough with your arm or a tissue</li>
<li>Frequently disinfecting surfaces.</li>
</ul>
<p>We realize that this is an ever evolving situation and will continue to provide you information as warranted as we work with our local and regional health officials, as well as surrounding school districts on this issue. In the meantime, please find below helpful information resources about Covid-19.</p>
<p><strong>Have questions?</strong> Submit your questions to <a href="mailto:communications@comalisd.org">communications@comalisd.org.</a></p>
<p><strong>More information can be found on the side navigation.</strong></p>
<p> </p>
